This paper belongs to the field of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with protecting digital integrated circuits from reverse engineering. The paper also proposes a machine learning framework based on graph deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves designing a new model and conducting experiments, which could fall under the categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and computer architecture (cs.AR).
